# MCP Capability Catalog (M1-M20)

`alc_mcp.catalog.MCP_TOOLS` is the canonical machine-readable catalog. This file is the human-readable reference for agents. Drift tests (`tests/test_mcp_catalog_doc.py`, `tests/test_catalog_mcp_parity.py`) assert every catalog entry has a row here and that every UQ/UP catalog entry has an MCP partner (or is on the explicit CLI-only allowlist).

| ID | Tool | Kind | Backing | Notes |
| --- | --- | --- | --- | --- |
| M1 | `get_gates` | read | `alc_query.get_gates` | Approved gates for a repo, optionally domain scoped. |
| M2 | `get_skill_context` | read | `alc_query.get_skill_context` | Latest skill-context markdown. |
| M3 | `get_recommendations` | read | `alc_query.get_recommendations` | Recommender rows from `recommendations.json`. |
| M4 | `list_pending_patches` | read | `alc_query.get_pending_patches` | Pending patch bundles, excluding rejected/deferred patches. |
| M5 | `get_dashboard_url` | read | `state_handle.dashboard_url` | Localhost dashboard URL when known, otherwise `file://` dashboard path. |
| M6 | `propose_apply` | propose | `alc_propose.propose_apply` | Returns an apply command. Does not apply or mutate target files. |
| M7 | `propose_gate` | propose | `alc_propose.propose_gate` | Appends a proposed gate to the review queue and emits proposal telemetry. |
| M8 | `report_outcome` | observe | `alc_propose.report_outcome` | Emits `outcome_reported` via `event_writer.write_event`. |
| M9 | `report_agent_event` | observe | `alc_propose.report_agent_event` | Emits `agent_dispatch_*` via `event_writer.write_event`. |
| M10 | `exec_sandbox` | exec | `exec_sandbox.run` | Runs bounded read/worktree/eval commands through the sandbox primitive. |
| M11 | `next_action` | read | `alc_next_action.next_action` | Session-lifecycle synthesiser (start/end/recap/leftoff/auto); collates signals across pending patches, recommendations, gates, apply log, outcomes, and activity. Backs the `/alc-next` slash command and writes `latest-next-action.json` cache. |
| M12 | `get_apply_log` | read | `alc_query.get_apply_log` | Patch apply events from project-scope `events.sqlite` (UQ1). |
| M13 | `get_outcomes` | read | `alc_query.get_outcomes` | Eval-verdict outcomes from project-scope `events.sqlite` (UQ2). Lets agents check whether a previously loaded gate was helpful. |
| M14 | `get_event_dag` | read | `alc_query.get_event_dag` | Session event DAG via recursive CTE (UQ5). Use to trace what happened in a specific session. |
| M15 | `get_actor_summary` | read | `alc_query.get_actor_summary` | Per-actor event counts from project-scope `events.sqlite` (UQ6). |
| M16 | `get_skill_invocation_history` | read | `alc_query.get_skill_invocation_history` | Historical invocation events for a specific skill (UQ7). |
| M17 | `get_skill_usage_summary` | read | `alc_query.get_skill_usage_summary` | Aggregate `actor_name` counts in indexed events, sorted by count desc (UQ8). Used by dashboard skill-routing signals. |
| M18 | `mark_patch_status` | propose | `alc_propose.mark_patch_status` | Mark a pending patch deferred/rejected and emit a status event (UP5). Closes the M6 propose_apply asymmetry. |
| M19 | `get_proposal_queue` | read | `alc_query.get_proposal_queue` | Operator proposal queue rows from `improvement-queue.jsonl` as normalized lifecycle records (UQ10). |
| M20 | `get_proposal_lifecycle` | read | `alc_query.get_proposal_lifecycle` | Normalized proposal lifecycle rows across queue, patch, and suggestion artifacts (UQ11). |

In addition to the catalog tools, the server exposes a meta tool `list_capabilities(repo)` that returns the live catalog plus per-tool `version` and `min_compatible_version`. Agents should call it first and compare against their known client contract before invoking other tools.
